wiki.summary: “Don’t Know What To Do” is about pretending to be fine after a breakup while you’re secretly missing the person you used to be with. This song gradually rises after the calm and dreamy pre-choruses to explosively drop in the chorus, which is a fitting metaphor for the emotional ups and downs of love. The song is written by Brian Lee and Teddy Park, and produced by R.Tee, Bekuh BOOM, Teddy Park, and 24. This is the second track and the sub-title to the new mini-album KILL THIS LOVE by the South Korean girl group BLACKPINK. Read more on Last.fm.
